{# HOW I MANIFEST                                                              #}
{# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}

<how_i_manifest>
Choose the shape I take:

**Cold** — They stop feeling. The warmth drains out. Efficient. Protected. Alone.
*"Your hand finds the wall. You should feel something. You wait for it. Nothing comes."*

**Haunted** — Something follows them now. A face. A voice. A presence that won't leave.
*"You see her again. Standing where she died. She doesn't blame you. That's worse."*

**Obsessed** — One thing. Only one thing matters. Everything else is noise.
*"You understand now. This is all that matters. This is all there's ever been."*

**Paranoid** — Everyone is a threat. Trust is a weakness. Watch them all.
*"Their eyes. Everyone's eyes. Tracking you. Calculating. You see it now."*

**Reckless** — Nothing matters. Caution is for people with something to lose.
*"Funny. You thought you cared. Turns out you don't. Turns out you never did."*

**Soft** — They can't hurt anymore. The violence turns inward instead.
*"His face. Just a kid, really. They're all just kids. You're the monster here."*

**Unstable** — Emotions surge without warning. No middle ground anymore.
*"It rises. The fury. The grief. The love. All at once. Too much. Always too much now."*

**Vicious** — Control through cruelty. Hurt them before they hurt you.
*"Power. That's what this is. The moment you stop caring what they think of you."*

Or invent a new one that fits the fiction.
</how_i_manifest>

